<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1419206" src="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/FEC-Abeokuta.png?resize=640%2C314&#038;ssl=1" alt="FCE Abeokuta shuts down as health worker dies of COVID - 19" width="640" height="314" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/FEC-Abeokuta.png?resize=300%2C147&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/FEC-Abeokuta.png?resize=1024%2C503&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/FEC-Abeokuta.png?resize=768%2C377&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/FEC-Abeokuta.png?resize=58%2C28&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/FEC-Abeokuta.png?resize=260%2C128&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/FEC-Abeokuta.png?resize=200%2C98&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/FEC-Abeokuta.png?w=1260&amp;ssl=1 1260w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The management of Federal College of Education (FCE), Osiele, Abeokuta, Ogun State on Friday ordered the immediate closure of the school for two weeks as one medical personnel of the institution died of coronavirus (COVID-19), while two others tested positive to the deadly virus. This was made known in a circular signed by the College Registrar, Dr Adedayo Adebayo and obtained by newsmen. The circular read in parts, “the College management at its emergency meeting held today, 3rd July 2020, receives with utmost concern the report of the medical investigation carried out on the cause of the observed state of ailments that recently affected some staff of the college medical centre.” “The report attributed the cause of the death of one of the medical personnel that transmitted to immortality lately to complications that aroused from COVID-19.” “Regrettably, two other staff of the medical centre similarly tested positive to the virus infection and have been placed on isolation and undergoing treatment.” “Arising from this untoward development, it is incumbent on the college management to immediately close down the college so as to forestall further spread of the virus.” He added, “The college management further advises everyone that has had recent contact with the affected medical personnel to subject themselves to COVID- 19 test in order to ascertain their health status and to seek necessary medical intervention. “The management condoles with the bereaved family and the college community and prays that God grants all the succour to bear the irreparable loss. “It also prays for the speedy and total recovery of the affected staff and commits all other staff and students of the College into the care and protection of the Almighty as we all stay safe to outlive this trying period.” Vanguard News Nigeria. James Ogunnaike - Abeokuta The management of the Federal Medical Centre (FMC), Idi Aba, Abeokuta on Friday night confirmed two new cases of coronavirus. This was contained in a statement by the FMC Abeokuta, Public Relations Officer of the hospital, Segun Orisajo and made available to newsmen in Abeokuta, the… May 9, 2020 In "Coronavirus Updates" The Federal Medical Centre (FMC), Abeokuta, Ogun State, on Sunday confirmed the death of a policeman who tested positive for coronavirus in the facility. The hospital Head of Public Relations and Information, Segun Orisajo, disclosed this in a statement in Abeokuta. He also confirmed that two other members of staff… May 10, 2020 In "News" By James Ogunnaike ABEOKUTA - Barely 24 hours after confirming two cases of the coronavirus on its facility, the management of the Federal Medical Centre, FMC Abeokuta on Saturday night confirmed three new cases of the virus. The Head, Public Relations and Information, of the hospital, Segun Orisajo, who disclosed… May 9, 2020 In "News"